<h2 class="pdoc-module-header" id="ClusterRole">
<a class="pdoc-member-name" href="https://github.com/pulumi/pulumi-kubernetes/blob/36ce0bf824c0f772e9a72416e6f8a1e98161408f/sdk/nodejs/rbac/v1beta1/ClusterRole.ts#L14">class <b>ClusterRole</b></a>
</h2>
<div class="pdoc-module-contents">
<pre class="highlight"><span class='kd'>extends</span> <a href='/docs/reference/pkg/nodejs/pulumi/pulumi/#CustomResource'>CustomResource</a></pre>
{{% md %}}

ClusterRole is a cluster level, logical grouping of PolicyRules that can be referenced as a
unit by a RoleBinding or ClusterRoleBinding.

{{% /md %}}

Get the state of an existing `ClusterRole` resource, as identified by `id`.
The ID is of the form `[namespace]/&lt;name&gt;`; if `namespace` is omitted, then (per
Kubernetes convention) the ID becomes `default/&lt;name&gt;`.

Pulumi will keep track of this resource using `name` as the Pulumi ID.

<h3 class="pdoc-member-header" id="ClusterRole-aggregationRule">
<a class="pdoc-child-name" href="https://github.com/pulumi/pulumi-kubernetes/blob/36ce0bf824c0f772e9a72416e6f8a1e98161408f/sdk/nodejs/rbac/v1beta1/ClusterRole.ts#L20">property <b>aggregationRule</b></a>
</h3>
<div class="pdoc-member-contents">
<pre class="highlight"><span class='kd'>public </span>aggregationRule: <a href='/docs/reference/pkg/nodejs/pulumi/pulumi/#Output'>pulumi.Output</a>&lt;<a href='/docs/reference/pkg/nodejs/pulumi/kubernetes/types/output/#AggregationRule'>outputs.rbac.v1beta1.AggregationRule</a>&gt;;</pre>
{{% md %}}

AggregationRule is an optional field that describes how to build the Rules for this
ClusterRole. If AggregationRule is set, then the Rules are controller managed and direct
changes to Rules will be stomped by the controller.

{{% /md %}}

<h2 class="pdoc-module-header" id="ClusterRoleBinding">
<a class="pdoc-member-name" href="https://github.com/pulumi/pulumi-kubernetes/blob/36ce0bf824c0f772e9a72416e6f8a1e98161408f/sdk/nodejs/rbac/v1beta1/ClusterRoleBinding.ts#L14">class <b>ClusterRoleBinding</b></a>
</h2>
<div class="pdoc-module-contents">
<pre class="highlight"><span class='kd'>extends</span> <a href='/docs/reference/pkg/nodejs/pulumi/pulumi/#CustomResource'>CustomResource</a></pre>
{{% md %}}

ClusterRoleBinding references a ClusterRole, but not contain it.  It can reference a
ClusterRole in the global namespace, and adds who information via Subject.

{{% /md %}}

<h2 class="pdoc-module-header" id="RoleBinding">
<a class="pdoc-member-name" href="https://github.com/pulumi/pulumi-kubernetes/blob/36ce0bf824c0f772e9a72416e6f8a1e98161408f/sdk/nodejs/rbac/v1beta1/RoleBinding.ts#L16">class <b>RoleBinding</b></a>
</h2>
<div class="pdoc-module-contents">
<pre class="highlight"><span class='kd'>extends</span> <a href='/docs/reference/pkg/nodejs/pulumi/pulumi/#CustomResource'>CustomResource</a></pre>
{{% md %}}

RoleBinding references a role, but does not contain it.  It can reference a Role in the same
namespace or a ClusterRole in the global namespace. It adds who information via Subjects and
namespace information by which namespace it exists in.  RoleBindings in a given namespace
only have effect in that namespace.

{{% /md %}}
